properties.abstract: This hike offers a wonderful spectacle of nature: light-green lakes set in the heart of a barren mountain landscape. Highly recommended!
properties.description:
The hike begins at the Wgerhus Postauto bus stop. From here the trail runs in a north-easterly direction across pastures and scree, up the slope to Winterlcke.

From here hikers can enjoy a unique view of the Jriseen lakes and the Jri Glacier. Beyond them stretch the peaks of the Silvretta Massif and the Piz Linard. The largest of the Jriseen lakes is milky-green in colour and is fed underground by the melt waters from the Jri Glacier. Its runoff is the Jribach stream, which gushes down into the Jri valley and on to Vereina. The waters of the other lakes are dark blue and so clear that the lake bottom is visible.

Returning to the starting point takes you along the left-hand edge of the glacier and between the light-green waters of the Jriseen lakes. A wonderful photo opportunity. From the lakes the trail continues upwards to the Jriflelafurgga and from there back down towards the valley and the Wgerhus.
